# Farq

A Python library for raster change detection and analysis. Farq simplifies the process of identifying and analyzing changes between raster datasets over time.

## Features

- Raster change detection using various algorithms
- Statistical analysis of changes
- Visualization tools for change analysis
- Support for multiple raster formats
- Easy-to-use API for spatial data processing

## Installation

```bash
pip install farq
```

## Quick Start

```python
import farq

# Load two raster datasets
raster1 = farq.load_raster("before.tif")
raster2 = farq.load_raster("after.tif")

# Detect changes
changes = farq.detect_changes(raster1, raster2, method="difference")

# Visualize changes
farq.plot_changes(changes)

# Get change statistics
stats = farq.analyze_changes(changes)
```

